<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and I just assumed that RPers were more mature than non RPers.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Isn't this a contradiction?  The thing is I have no problems with non rpers, just with some of the attitudes they express about it on the roleplaying server.  Doesn't really matter why you came, the server is marked for roleplaying unlike any of the other servers.  When non rpers enter this server they have to know that the focus of those here is rping, so why do they have attitudes about it?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rathmorg>Rathmorg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/30/03 2:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4068.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplaying</span><hr size=1> I admit that I may not be the best roleplayer, but atleast I try.  One of the best times I had roleplaying was when I was fletching.  There I was, combine, combine, etc.  I jump of the table I was sitting on to sell my arrows back to the vender and stumbled over this lady who was doing trades skills herself.<br>
<br>
I apologized for my clumsiness and we struck up a dialog about how was she to walk amoung her friends with my foot prints all over her robe.  <br>
<br>
We joked and laughed and worked out a solution.  All in ten minutes or less.  Was great fun.<br>
<br>
I too hate the d00d speak, but I do not bash those that use it, nor people who roleplay.  I have seen some really impressive roleplay, some not so and none at all.  I myself have not been bashed for my roleplay or lack of it either.  Just lucky I guess.<br>
<br>
IMHO there are 2 schools of roleplay just like the 2 schools of Jack Danials drinkers:  Those that drink because they like the taste and those that drink for the effect.<br>
<br>
Which are you?<br>
